rules: Rule1: Given that the startup secures a government grant, then if the startup analyzes market demand, this triggers the chain where if the startup identifies biofuel potential, then when the startup tests the corn compound, the consequence is that if the startup purifies the corn compound, then the startup commercializes the biofuel product
Rule2: The startup secures a government grant or the startup receives venture capital

Rule3: If the startup receives venture capital, then provided that the startup analyzes market demand, this leads to the condition that if the startup identifies biofuel potential, then when the startup tests the corn compound, the result is that if the startup purifies the corn compound, then the startup commercializes the biofuel product
Rule4: If the startup builds a pilot plant, then the startup commercializes the biofuel product
Rule5: If the startup partners with an ethanol producer, then the startup commercializes the biofuel product
Rule6: If the startup acquires land, then the startup builds a pilot plant
Rule7: The startup acquires land or the startup leases a facility
Rule8: If the startup leases a facility, then the startup renovates the facility
Rule9: If the startup hires engineers, then under the condition that the startup renovates the facility, the startup partners with an ethanol producer
Rule10: If the startup develops an extraction technique, then the startup improves extraction efficiency
Rule11: The startup develops an extraction technique or the startup licenses extraction technology
Rule12: If the startup licenses extraction technology, then provided that the startup discovers the corn variant, the startup patents the corn variant
Rule13: If the startup improves extraction efficiency, then given that the startup discovers the corn variant, the startup patents the corn variant
Rule14: If the startup faces regulatory hurdles, then the startup requires additional testing
Rule15: The startup faces regulatory hurdles or if the startup discovers the corn variant, then when the startup has secured Series A funding, the startup hires researchers
Rule16: If the startup requires additional testing, then the startup delays the production timeline
Rule17: If the startup develops a fermentation process, then provided that the startup has secured Series A funding, the startup hires researchers
Rule18: The startup develops a fermentation process or the startup discovers the corn variant
Rule19: If the startup discovers the corn variant, then the startup sequences the corn genome
Rule20: If the startup patents the corn variant, then given that the startup has secured Series A funding, the startup hires researchers
Rule21: If the startup sequences the corn genome, then the startup patents the corn variant
Rule22: If the startup extracts the corn compound, then the startup purifies the corn compound
Rule23: If the startup does not commercialize the biofuel product, then the startup has secured Series A funding
